# Cursor Rules

## Test-Driven Development
Always write tests first before implementation (TDD)
Red → Green → Refactor cycle

## Code Quality
Use descriptive variable and method names (no abbreviations like usr, btn, etc.)
Keep methods under 20 lines
Prefer composition over inheritance
Extract magic numbers to named constants
Avoid nested ternary operators

## Spring Boot Specifics
Use constructor injection over field injection (@Autowired on fields)
Create separate test configuration classes
Use @SpringBootTest sparingly (prefer @WebMvcTest, @DataJpaTest)
Always close resources (use try-with-resources)

## Git Workflow
Commit messages: type(scope): description (e.g., feat(user): add registration)
Create feature branches: feature/AUTH-123-user-registration
Squash commits before merging to main

## Performance
Use pagination for list endpoints (Spring Data Pageable)
Add database indexes for frequently queried fields
Use @Transactional(readOnly = true) for read operations
Avoid N+1 queries (use @EntityGraph or JOIN FETCH)

---

**Cursor AI Editor Preferences** - These rules help maintain consistency when using Cursor for coding.
